ously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Joan DeMeols was born in 1275, in Ormskirk, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Alan de Meols, was 38 and her mother, Mrs. Alice de Moels, was 25. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with William de Coudray. She died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1275–":"1275–Surnud","1275–Female":"1275–Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1295–1350":"1295–1350","1325–1362":"1325–1362","1237–Male":"1237–Surnud","1250–1335":"1250–1335","1325":"1325","1237":"1237","1335":"1335","1275":"1275","1362":"1362","1350":"1350","1295":"1295","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","about 1295":"umbes 1295","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ormskirk, Lancashire, England":"Ormskirk, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1275–":"1275–Kuollut","1275–Female":"1275–Kuollut","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1295–1350":"1295–1350","1325–1362":"1325–1362","1237–Male":"1237–Kuollut","1250–1335":"1250–1335","1325":"1325","1237":"1237","1335":"1335","1275":"1275","1362":"1362","1350":"1350","1295":"1295","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","about 1295":"noin 1295","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ormskirk, Lancashire, England":"Ormskirk, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1275–":"1275–Décédée","1275–Female":"1275–Décédée","1270–M